This paper focuses on the assurance process of self-adaptive systems, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY) categories. The paper also proposes a goal-oriented approach that involves symbolic model checking, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and program verification (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper addresses uncertainty, which is a topic relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.SE and cs.SY, followed by cs.AI, cs.CR, and cs.PL.
